+    <aside class="toc">
+      <h4>On this page</h4>
+      <ul>
+        <li><a href="#what-it-does">What pd spawn Does</a></li>
+        <li><a href="#quick-start">Quick Start (Ollama)</a></li>
+        <li><a href="#backends">Backends</a></li>
+        <li><a href="#coordination">Coordination Auto-Wired</a></li>
+        <li><a href="#managing">Managing Agents</a></li>
+        <li><a href="#sdk">SDK Equivalent</a></li>
+      </ul>
+    </aside>
+
+    <article class="article">
+      <p><code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); background: rgba(0,102,204,0.08); padding: 0.15em 0.4em; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9em;">pd spawn</code> launches AI agents (Ollama, Claude API, Aider, Gemini, or any custom subprocess) with Port Daddy coordination pre-wired. The spawned agent is registered as a Port Daddy agent, sends heartbeats automatically, logs its responses as notes, and enters the salvage queue if it crashes.</p>
+
+      <h2 id="what-it-does">What pd spawn Does</h2>
+      <p>Without <code>pd spawn</code>, integrating an AI agent into Port Daddy requires manual calls: register the agent, start a session, send heartbeats in a loop, write notes, end the session on completion. <code>pd spawn</code> does all of this for you.</p>
+
+      <p>The agent you spawn becomes a full Port Daddy citizen: it appears in the dashboard, its output becomes queryable notes, other agents can pub/sub with it, and if it dies unexpectedly its last note becomes its salvage context.</p>
+
+      <h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start — Ollama</h2>
+      <p>Spawn a local Ollama agent to perform a coding task:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># Prerequisite: Ollama must be running (ollama serve)</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn \
+    --backend ollama \
+    --model llama3.2:8b \
+    --identity myapp:coder \
+    --purpose <span class="string">"Refactor auth module"</span> \
+    -- <span class="string">"Fix the login bug in src/auth.ts"</span>
+
+<span class="output">Agent spawned: agent-a1b2c3
+Backend:  ollama (llama3.2:8b)
+Identity: myapp:coder
+Session:  sess-d4e5f6
+Heartbeat: every 30s
+
+[llama3.2:8b] Analyzing src/auth.ts...
+[llama3.2:8b] Found issue: session token not invalidated on logout.
+[llama3.2:8b] Fix: call destroySession() in the logout handler.
+Agent done: sess-d4e5f6 ended</span></code></pre>
+
+      <p>The <code>--</code> separator marks the end of <code>pd spawn</code> flags. Everything after it is the prompt sent to the agent.</p>
+
+      <h2 id="backends">Backends</h2>
+      <p>Five backends are supported. Each is tuned for its runtime:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># Ollama — local inference, uses HTTP to port 11434</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn --backend ollama --model llama3.2:8b \
+    --identity myapp:coder -- <span class="string">"Review src/auth.ts"</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Claude API — uses @anthropic-ai/sdk directly (not the CLI)</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn --backend claude --model claude-haiku-4-5 \
+    --identity myapp:reviewer -- <span class="string">"Review PR for security issues"</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Gemini — uses @google/generative-ai</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn --backend gemini --model gemini-flash \
+    --identity myapp:analyst -- <span class="string">"Summarize the test failures"</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Aider — git-native coding agent, wraps stdout as PD notes</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn --backend aider --model gpt-4o \
+    --identity myapp:writer -- src/auth.ts src/middleware.ts
+
+<span class="comment"># Custom — any subprocess, stdout becomes PD notes</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn --backend custom \
+    --identity myapp:worker -- python3 ./process.py</code></pre>
+
+      <h2 id="coordination">Coordination Auto-Wired</h2>
+      <p>Every spawned agent automatically gets:</p>
+      <ol>
+        <li>An agent registration with the identity you specify</li>
+        <li>A Port Daddy session opened with the purpose you specify</li>
+        <li>Heartbeats sent every 30 seconds</li>
+        <li>Each LLM response chunk added as an immutable note</li>
+        <li>Session ended cleanly when the agent completes</li>
+        <li>Resurrection queue entry if the agent crashes unexpectedly</li>
+      </ol>
+
+      <p>Other agents can see spawned agents in <code>pd salvage</code>, read their notes, and pick up where they left off if they crash.</p>
+
+      <h2 id="managing">Managing Agents</h2>
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># See all running spawned agents</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawned
+<span class="output">AGENT ID      BACKEND   MODEL           IDENTITY       STATUS
+agent-a1b2c3  ollama    llama3.2:8b     myapp:coder    running
+agent-b2c3d4  claude    haiku-4-5       myapp:review   running</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Get JSON output for scripting</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawned --json
+
+<span class="comment"># Stop a specific agent</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd spawn kill agent-a1b2c3
+<span class="output">Agent agent-a1b2c3 stopped. Session ended.</span></code></pre>
+
+      <h2 id="sdk">SDK Equivalent</h2>
+      <pre><code><span class="keyword">import</span> { PortDaddy } <span class="keyword">from</span> <span class="string">'port-daddy'</span>;
+
+<span class="keyword">const</span> pd = <span class="keyword">new</span> PortDaddy();
+
+<span class="comment">// Spawn an Ollama agent</span>
+<span class="keyword">const</span> agent = <span class="keyword">await</span> pd.spawn({
+  backend: <span class="string">'ollama'</span>,
+  model: <span class="string">'llama3.2:8b'</span>,
+  identity: <span class="string">'myapp:coder'</span>,
+  purpose: <span class="string">'Refactor auth module'</span>,
+  prompt: <span class="string">'Fix the login bug in src/auth.ts'</span>,
+});
+
+<span class="comment">// Stream output as it arrives</span>
+agent.on(<span class="string">'output'</span>, (chunk) => console.log(chunk));
+agent.on(<span class="string">'done'</span>, () => console.log(<span class="string">'Agent finished'</span>));
+
+<span class="comment">// Or await completion</span>
+<span class="keyword">const</span> result = <span class="keyword">await</span> agent.wait();
+console.log(result.notes);</code></pre>
+
