+
+      <h2 id="start">Starting a Session with a Phase</h2>
+
+      <p>Pass <code>--phase</code> to <code>pd begin</code> to start directly in a specific phase. The default is <code>planning</code> if you omit it.</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># Start in planning phase (default)</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd begin --identity myapp:feature-auth --purpose <span class="string">"Add JWT auth"</span> --phase planning
+<span class="output">Agent registered: agent-a1b2c3
+Session started: sess-d4e5f6 [planning]
+Context saved to .portdaddy/current.json</span></code></pre>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># Jump straight to in_progress if you already know what you're doing</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd begin --identity myapp:bugfix-timeout --purpose <span class="string">"Fix connection timeout"</span> --phase in_progress
+<span class="output">Agent registered: agent-b2c3d4
+Session started: sess-e5f6a7 [in_progress]
+Context saved to .portdaddy/current.json</span></code></pre>
+
+      <div class="callout">
+        <strong>Identity matters for salvage.</strong> The <code>--identity</code> flag tells Port Daddy which project and stack you're working on. When another agent in the same project runs <code>pd salvage</code>, they'll see your session and know what you were doing.
+      </div>
+
+      <h2 id="advance">Advancing Through Phases</h2>
+
+      <p>Update the phase as your work progresses. This keeps other agents and humans informed of exactly where you are.</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># Done planning, starting to code</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase in_progress
+<span class="output">Session sess-d4e5f6 updated: planning -&gt; in_progress</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Coding done, running tests</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase testing
+<span class="output">Session sess-d4e5f6 updated: in_progress -&gt; testing</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Tests pass, requesting review</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase reviewing
+<span class="output">Session sess-d4e5f6 updated: testing -&gt; reviewing</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Merged! pd done marks it completed automatically</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd done <span class="string">"Auth merged, all tests green"</span>
+<span class="output">Session ended: sess-d4e5f6 [completed]
+Agent unregistered
+Context cleaned up</span></code></pre>
+
+      <p>You can also update the phase via the HTTP API directly -- useful when automating from CI or a shell script:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> curl -X PUT http://localhost:9876/sessions/sess-d4e5f6 \
+    -H <span class="string">"Content-Type: application/json"</span> \
+    -d <span class="string">'{"phase": "testing"}'</span>
+<span class="output">{"id":"sess-d4e5f6","phase":"testing","updatedAt":"2026-03-10T..."}</span></code></pre>
+
+      <h3>Abandoning a session</h3>
+
+      <p>If you hit a blocker and can't continue, mark the session as abandoned. This places it in the salvage queue so another agent can pick it up with full context.</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase abandoned
+<span class="output">Session sess-d4e5f6 marked as abandoned
+Entering salvage queue...</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Another agent sees it</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd salvage --project myapp
+<span class="output">1 session(s) needing salvage in myapp:*
+
+Session: sess-d4e5f6
+Agent:   agent-a1b2c3 (dead)
+Phase:   abandoned
+Purpose: Add JWT auth
+Notes:   4 note(s)
+Files:   src/auth.ts, src/middleware.ts</span></code></pre>
+
+      <div class="callout-warning">
+        <strong>Abandoned is not the same as completed.</strong> Use <code>abandoned</code> when you've stopped due to a blocker and want another agent to continue. Use <code>completed</code> (via <code>pd done</code>) when the work is actually done.
+      </div>
+
+      <h2 id="integration">Integration Signals</h2>
+
+      <p>Integration signals solve the startup coordination problem: "Is service X ready yet?" Instead of polling <code>/health</code> endpoints in a loop or hardcoding <code>sleep 5</code> in your startup scripts, services declare when they're ready and waiters block until that signal arrives.</p>
+
+      <h3>The basic pattern</h3>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># auth-service signals it's ready</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd integration ready auth-service
+<span class="output">Signal broadcast: auth-service is ready</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># api-service blocks until auth-service is ready</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd integration wait auth-service
+<span class="output">Waiting for auth-service...
+auth-service is ready!</span></code></pre>
+
+      <p>If <code>auth-service</code> is already ready when <code>wait</code> is called, it returns immediately:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> pd integration wait auth-service
+<span class="output">auth-service is already ready. Proceeding immediately.</span></code></pre>
+
+      <h3>Coordinating a multi-service startup</h3>
+
+      <p>Here's a real pattern for a three-service app where the API depends on auth and the frontend depends on the API:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># auth-service/start.sh</span>
+node src/auth-server.js &amp;
+<span class="comment"># Wait for the server to bind and pass health check</span>
+until curl -sf http://localhost:3100/health &gt;/dev/null; <span class="keyword">do</span> sleep 0.5; <span class="keyword">done</span>
+pd integration ready auth-service
+
+<span class="comment"># api-service/start.sh</span>
+pd integration wait auth-service  <span class="comment"># blocks until auth is up</span>
+node src/api-server.js &amp;
+until curl -sf http://localhost:3101/health &gt;/dev/null; <span class="keyword">do</span> sleep 0.5; <span class="keyword">done</span>
+pd integration ready api-service
+
+<span class="comment"># frontend/start.sh</span>
+pd integration wait api-service   <span class="comment"># blocks until API is up</span>
+npm run dev</code></pre>
+
+      <p>Each service declares its own readiness after confirming its health endpoint passes. Downstream services wait on the upstream signal. No sleep timers, no race conditions.</p>
+
+      <h3>Using integration with sessions</h3>
+
+      <p>Integration signals work well alongside session phases. An agent can advance to <code>in_progress</code> and then block on a dependency before doing its work:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> pd begin --identity myapp:api --purpose <span class="string">"Build API endpoints"</span> --phase planning
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase in_progress
+
+<span class="comment"># Wait for the database migration agent to finish</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd integration wait myapp-db-migrated
+<span class="output">Waiting for myapp-db-migrated...
+myapp-db-migrated is ready!</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Now do the actual API work</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session update sess-d4e5f6 --phase testing
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd done <span class="string">"API endpoints complete"</span></code></pre>
+
+      <h2 id="history">Viewing Session History</h2>
+
+      <p>Several commands let you inspect active and past sessions:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="comment"># List all active sessions</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd sessions
+<span class="output">SESSION       AGENT          PHASE        PURPOSE
+sess-d4e5f6   agent-a1b2c3   reviewing    Add JWT auth
+sess-e5f6a7   agent-b2c3d4   testing      Fix connection timeout</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Details and notes for a specific session</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd session sess-d4e5f6
+<span class="output">Session: sess-d4e5f6
+Agent:   agent-a1b2c3
+Phase:   reviewing
+Purpose: Add JWT auth
+Files:   src/auth.ts, src/middleware.ts
+
+Notes:
+  [10:14] planning: Decided to use jose library for JWT
+  [10:31] in_progress: Auth route working, token generation done
+  [11:02] testing: All 24 tests passing
+  [11:15] reviewing: PR opened, waiting for review</span>
+
+<span class="comment"># Full project history</span>
+<span class="prompt">$</span> pd history
+<span class="output">Showing last 20 events for current project
+
+  10:14  sess-d4e5f6  phase:planning     Add JWT auth
+  10:31  sess-d4e5f6  phase:in_progress  Add JWT auth
+  11:02  sess-d4e5f6  phase:testing      Add JWT auth
+  11:15  sess-d4e5f6  phase:reviewing    Add JWT auth
+  09:55  sess-e5f6a7  phase:in_progress  Fix connection timeout
+  11:30  sess-e5f6a7  phase:testing      Fix connection timeout</span></code></pre>
+
+      <p>The history view is useful when picking up salvaged work -- you can see exactly what phase transitions happened and reconstruct the previous agent's progress.</p>
+
+      <h2 id="sdk">SDK Usage</h2>
+
+      <p>All phase and integration operations are available in the JavaScript SDK:</p>
+
+      <pre><code><span class="keyword">const</span> pd = <span class="keyword">new</span> PortDaddy();
+
+<span class="comment">// Start session with a phase</span>
+<span class="keyword">const</span> { sessionId } = <span class="keyword">await</span> pd.begin({
+  identity: <span class="string">'myapp:feature-auth'</span>,
+  purpose: <span class="string">'Add JWT authentication'</span>,
+  phase: <span class="string">'planning'</span>,
+});
+
+<span class="comment">// Advance through phases</span>
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.updateSession(sessionId, { phase: <span class="string">'in_progress'</span> });
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.updateSession(sessionId, { phase: <span class="string">'testing'</span> });
+
+<span class="comment">// Signal that a dependency is ready</span>
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.publish(<span class="string">'integration:ready:auth-service'</span>, { ready: <span class="keyword">true</span> });
+
+<span class="comment">// Wait for a dependency (resolves immediately if already signaled)</span>
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.integrationWait(<span class="string">'auth-service'</span>);
+
+<span class="comment">// List sessions (optionally filter by phase)</span>
+<span class="keyword">const</span> testing = <span class="keyword">await</span> pd.listSessions({ phase: <span class="string">'testing'</span> });
+
+<span class="comment">// End session -- marks completed automatically</span>
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.done({ sessionId, note: <span class="string">'Auth merged, all tests green'</span> });
+
+<span class="comment">// Abandon if you hit a blocker</span>
+<span class="keyword">await</span> pd.updateSession(sessionId, { phase: <span class="string">'abandoned'</span> });</code></pre>
+
+      <h2 id="decision">When to Use Each Phase</h2>
+
+      <div class="decision-box">
+        <h4>Phase selection guide</h4>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase">planning</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">You're writing a design doc, deciding which files to change, or figuring out the approach. No code has been modified yet.</span>
+        </div>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase">in_progress</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">You've started making changes. Files are claimed, code is being written, the plan is executing.</span>
+        </div>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase">testing</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">Implementation is done. You're running the test suite, fixing failing tests, checking behavior with curl or a browser.</span>
+        </div>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase">reviewing</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">Code is working and tested. You've opened a PR, or you're waiting for a human or another agent to review your changes before merging.</span>
+        </div>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase completed">completed</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">Your PR is merged, or the task is definitively done and won't be revisited. Set automatically by <code>pd done</code>.</span>
+        </div>
+        <div class="decision-item">
+          <span class="decision-phase abandoned">abandoned</span>
+          <span class="decision-desc">You've hit a blocker you can't resolve -- missing context, access issue, or the task needs a different approach. Use this so another agent can salvage your work with full context about where you stopped.</span>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+
+      <div class="callout-tip">
+        <strong>Keep phases updated as you go.</strong> A session stuck in <code>planning</code> while the agent is actually running tests is misleading to other agents. Update the phase when your work changes character -- it takes one command and makes the salvage system dramatically more useful.
+      </div>
+
+      <div class="prev-next">
+        <a href="debugging.html">
+          <div class="label">Previous tutorial</div>
+          <div class="title">Debugging with Port Daddy</div>
+        </a>
+        <a href="09-inbox-messaging.html" class="next">
+          <div class="label">Next tutorial</div>
+          <div class="title">Inbox &amp; Direct Messaging</div>
+        </a>
+      </div>
+    </article>
+  </div>
+
+  <footer>
+    <div class="footer-container">
+      <div class="footer-bottom">
+        <p>&copy; 2025-2026 Curiositech LLC. Released under the MIT License.</p>
+      </div>
+    </div>
